results.question: Why should we stop using plastic cups?
results.title: The Single Use Plastic Ban – What Your Business Must Know
results.snippet: Single use plastic cutlery, plates, and cups are cheap and convenient, but their disposal is problematic. They don't break down and can leach chemicals, adding to pollution if they end up in landfill. Even though most single use plastics are recyclable only 10% of single use plastic items are recycled.
emphasis: They don't break down and can leach chemicals, adding to pollution if they end up in landfill

results.snippet: Plastic cups are cheaper but are only good for cold drinks. Paper cups are somewhat less eco-friendly but prevent thermal burns. We recommend a combination of the two for maximum effectiveness.
emphasis: Plastic cups are cheaper but are only good for cold drinks
